## **2ï¸âƒ£ Other Important Principles in PHP & Laravel**
### **6. DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)**
âœ” Avoid duplicate code by using **helpers, traits, and service classes**.

### **7. KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid)**
âœ” Write clean and simple code instead of over-engineering.

### **8. YAGNI (You Ainâ€™t Gonna Need It)**
âœ” Donâ€™t add features **until** they are necessary.

### **9. Repository Pattern (Laravel Best Practice)**
âœ” Separates **database queries** from business logic.
```php
interface UserRepository {
    public function find($id);
}

class MySQLUserRepository implements UserRepository {
    public function find($id) {
        return User::find($id);
    }
}

class UserService {
    protected $userRepository;
    public function __construct(UserRepository $userRepository) {
        $this->userRepository = $userRepository;
    }

    public function getUser($id) {
        return $this->userRepository->find($id);
    }
}
```
âœ… **Makes database changes easier (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB).**  

